                            <comment id="15098915" author="knoguchi" created="Thu, 14 Jan 2016 21:34:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry for the delay.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my test environment (on both mac and linux), test was incorrectly passing by throwing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caused by: org.apache.pig.backend.executionengine.ExecException: ERROR 0: java.io.IOException: unexpected end of stream&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;even when hadoop&apos;s TextInputFormat was used.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the test, found that concatenated bzip file was corrupt.&lt;br/&gt;
I don&apos;t think we can use character-line based BufferedWriter/Reader for creating a binary(bzip) file.  &lt;br/&gt;
Though, I don&apos;t know how the build on the description was correctly failing...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixing test&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;catInto&lt;/tt&gt; method and adjusting the testBZ2Concatenation to follow &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rohini&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rohini&quot;&gt;rohini&lt;/a&gt;&apos;s suggestion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Can you fix the testcase? I think it would be good to keep the original one which throws the exception for Pig&apos;s bzipinputformat and another one for hadoop&apos;s which passes and also verifies the output.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15107580" author="rohini" created="Tue, 19 Jan 2016 22:27:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15109043" author="knoguchi" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 18:04:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review Rohini.  Committed to trunk(0.16).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
